s.sh\\n# Expected: ERROR with usage message\\n```\\n\\n### 1b. Input parsing\\n```bash\\n# Test: numeric run ID\\nbash scripts/download-e2e-artifacts.sh 12345\\n# Expected: attempts to fetch run 12345\\n\\n# Test: URL extraction\\nbash scripts/download-e2e-artifacts.sh https://github.com/entireio/cli/actions/runs/67890\\n# Expected: extracts run ID 67890\\n\\n# Test: \\\"latest\\\" keyword\\nbash scripts/download-e2e-artifacts.sh latest\\n# Expected: queries gh for most recent failed E2E run\\n\\n# Test: invalid input (non-numeric, non-URL, non-latest)\\nbash scripts/download-e2e-artifacts.sh \\\"foo bar\\\"\\n# Expected: ERROR about invalid input\\n```\\n\\n### 1c. Artifact restructuring\\nVerify that `e2e-artifacts-<agent>/` wrapper dirs are flattened to `<agent>/`:\\n```bash\\n# After a real download, check structure:\\nls e2e/artifacts/ci-<id>/\\n# Expected: claude-code/, opencode/, gemini-cli/ (not e2e-artifacts-claude-code/)\\n```\\n\\n### 1d. Metadata file\\n```bash\\n# After download, verify .run-info.json:\\ncat e2e/artifacts/ci-<id>/.run-info.json\\n# Expected: valid JSON with run_id, run_url, commit, downloaded_at, agents\\n```\\n\\n### 1e. Output contract\\n```bash\\n# Last line of stdout should be the absolute path\\nresult=$(bash scripts/download-e2e-artifacts.sh <valid-run-id>)\\necho \\\"$result\\\"  # Should be an absolute path\\n[ -d \\\"$result\\\" ]  # Should be an existing directory\\n```\\n\\n### How to test without real CI runs\\n- Use a known run ID from a previous E2E failure (check `gh run list -w e2e.yml --status=failure -L5`)\\n- Or trigger a deliberate failure by modifying a test and pushing\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Component 2: `.github/workflows/e2e-triage.yml`\\n\\nThis is a GitHub Actions workflow — testing requires CI execution.\\n\\n### 2a. Trigger condition\\n- **Verify**: Workflow triggers only when the \\\"E2E Tests\\\" workflow completes with `failure`\\n- **Test**: Push a change that breaks an E2E test → confirm triage workflow runs\\