o test\\n1. **Dry run**: Use `act` (local GitHub Actions runner) if available, or push to a test branch\\n2. **Real trigger**: Temporarily break an E2E test on a branch, let CI fail, watch triage workflow\\n3. **Check workflow logs**: `gh run list -w \\\"E2E Triage\\\"` and `gh run view <id> --log`\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Component 3: `.claude/skills/e2e-triage/SKILL.md`\\n\\nThis is a Claude skill prompt — testing requires invoking the skill.\\n\\n### 3a. Local mode (manual invocation)\\n```bash\\n# Test with a known failing test:\\n# 1. Invoke the skill\\nclaude \\\"/e2e-triage TestInteractiveMultiStep --agent claude-code\\\"\\n\\n# Verify:\\n# - Cost warning is shown before running\\n# - Test runs via `mise run test:e2e`\\n# - On failure, re-run happens automatically\\n# - Classification logic produces sensible output\\n# - Summary table is printed\\n```\\n\\n### 3b. Local mode with existing artifacts\\n```bash\\n# Point at pre-downloaded artifacts:\\nclaude \\\"/e2e-triage /path/to/e2e/artifacts/ci-12345\\\"\\n\\n# Verify: skips running tests, goes straight to analysis\\n```\\n\\n### 3c. Classification logic validation\\nTest with known scenarios:\\n- **Known flaky test**: Run a test that sometimes times out → should classify as flaky\\n- **Known real bug**: If you can reproduce a consistent failure → should classify as real-bug\\n- **Verify re-run decision table**: The skill's re-run signal table (Step 2) matches behavior\\n\\n### 3d. Action verification\\n- **Flaky → PR**: Verify branch naming (`fix/e2e-flaky-<date>`), canary runs, PR creation\\n- **Real bug → Issue**: Verify dedup search (`gh issue list --search`), issue/comment creation\\n- **triage-summary.json**: Verify JSON structure matches the template in Step 5\\n\\n### 3e. Cross-agent correlation (Step 3)\\n- If same test fails for multiple agents, verify the skill correlates them correctly\\n\\n### How to test\\n- Best tested by running against real or synthetic artifact directories\\n- For a quick smoke test: download artifacts from a recent CI failure and invoke the skill pointing at them\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Component 4: `e2e/README.md` changes\\n\\n### 4a. Documentation accuracy\\n- Verify the new sections reference correct file paths\\n- Verify the `scripts/download-e2e-artifacts.sh` usage examples match actual script behavior\\n- Verify the CI Workflows section correctly describes all three workflows\\n- Verify the \\\"Fixing flaky tests\\\" section is consistent with SKILL.md guidance\\n\\n### 4b. Link validity\\n- `e2e-triage.yml` is referenced — verify it exists at the stated path\\n- `e2e-isolated.yml` is referenced — verify it exists\\n- `.claude/skills/e2e-triage/` is referenced — verify it exists\\n\\n---\\n\\n## End-to-End Integration Test\\n\\nThe full pipeline test (most valuable but most expensive):\\n\\n1. **Trigger a real E2E failure** (modify a test prompt to be ambiguous, push to branch)\\n2. **Watch the chain**: E2E workflow fails → triage workflow triggers → artifacts downloaded → Claude analyzes → PR or issue created → Slack notifications sent\\n3. **Verify outputs**:\\n   - PR/issue was created with correct content\\n   - Slack messages arrived (start + completion)\\n   - triage-summary.json has correct structure\\n   - Summary table is accurate\\n\\n### Cheaper alternative: Isolated component tests\\nRun the download script against a real failed run, then invoke the skill locally pointing at those artifacts. This tests ~80% of the pipeline without triggering CI.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Risk Areas to Watch\\n\\n| Risk | Impact | Mitigation |\\n|------|--------|------------|\\n| Slack webhook JSON injection | Malformed Slack messages | `jq -n --arg` escaping (already implemented in commit 3edf654f) |\\n| Claude tool allowlist too broad | Unintended CI side effects | Allowlist is scoped: `mise run *`, `gh *`, `git *` + read/write |\\n| `e2e-isolated.yml` doesn't exist | CI re-runs fail | Confirmed it exists at `.github/workflows/e2e-isolated.yml` |\\n| Artifact expiry (7 days) | Download fails for old runs | Script already has error message for this |\\n| Race condition: two triage runs | Conflicting PRs/issues | `concurrency: cancel-in-progress: true` handles this |\\n\"},\"caller\":{\"type\":\"direct\"}}],\"stop_reason\":\"tool_use\",\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":148,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":46372,\"output_tokens\":2663,\"server_tool_use\":{\"web_search_requests\":0,\"web_fetch_requests\":0},\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":148,\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0},\"inference_geo\":\"\",\"iterations\":[],\"speed\":\"standard\"}},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYnV1JGqJt8SKfTGm5vn8\",\"type\":\"assistant\",\"uuid\":\"d345fce0-e8c2-42a2-870e-f835f9dbfbe3\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-06T20:49:12.633Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"d345fce0-e8c2-42a2-870e-f835f9dbfbe3\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alisha/Projects/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"d8638348-d252-4102-8f31-069674e6a037\",\"version\":\"2.1.70\",\"gitBranch\":\"alisha/e2e-triage\",\"slug\":\"moonlit-meandering-catmull\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"type\":\"hook_progress\",\"hookEvent\":\"PreToolUse\",\"hookName\":\"PreToolUse:Write\",\"command\":\"python3 ${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT}/hooks/security_reminder_hook.py\"},\"toolUseID\":\"toolu_01VWJKNv3dNVghuPZUgPsbmq\",\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_01VWJKNv3dNVghuPZUgPsbmq\",\"uuid\":\"070e8827-9aea-42a0-8806-3f85e3f77004\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-06T20:49:12.642Z\"}\n{\"type\":\"file-history-snapshot\",\"messageId\":\"d345fce0-e8c2-42a2-870e-f835f9dbfbe3\",\"snapshot\":{\"messageId\":\"26867109-b987-48b2-9567-81e1d5b8e65f\",\"trackedFileBackups\":{\"/Users/alisha/.claude/plans/moonlit-meandering-catmull.md\":{\"backupFileName\":null,\"version\":1,\"backupTime\":\"2026-03-06T20:49:12.715Z\"}},\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-06T20:47:50.467Z\"},\"isSnapshotUpdate\":true}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"070e8827-9aea-42a0-88